abstract: The candidates sparred angrily over whether to wipe out private health insurance and institute a government-run health system.
snippet: The candidates sparred angrily over whether to wipe out private health insurance and institute a government-run health system.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It took only one question — the very first — in Tuesday night’s Democratic presidential primary debate to make it clear that the issue that united the party in last year’s congressional elections in many ways now divides it.

abstract: The 77-year-old democratic socialist from Vermont made clear that he could still own the Democratic debate. And the debate stage.
snippet: The 77-year-old democratic socialist from Vermont made clear that he could still own the Democratic debate. And the debate stage.
lead_paragraph: Bernie Sanders was at it again — center stage, his baritone building to something — right hand raised and restless, as if he were scribbling his words on an invisible chalkboard.

abstract: Moderate underdogs kicked off the Detroit debates by targeting the top candidates with charges of “wish-list economics” and “impossible promises” on health care.
snippet: Moderate underdogs kicked off the Detroit debates by targeting the top candidates with charges of “wish-list economics” and “impossible promises” on health care.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — The leading liberals in the Democratic presidential primary, Senators Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren, strenuously fought back on Tuesday against accusations of making fanciful promises and imperiling the party’s prospects against President Trump, as a group of moderate underdogs sought to slow their momentum in the second round of debates.

abstract: The first debate exchange captured the battle within the Democratic Party over how the presidential nominee should change the country’s health care system.
snippet: The first debate exchange captured the battle within the Democratic Party over how the presidential nominee should change the country’s health care system.
lead_paragraph: The first exchange of the Democratic presidential debate on Tuesday offered a quick and exacting look at the vast ideological divide between the progressive wing of the Democratic Party and the more moderate candidates on the central topic of health care.

abstract: New York Times reporters followed the exchanges and provided context around the candidates’ claims.
snippet: New York Times reporters followed the exchanges and provided context around the candidates’ claims.
lead_paragraph: The second round of 2020 Democratic presidential primary debates kicked off on Tuesday in Detroit, with 10 candidates onstage for the first of two back-to-back nights. The other 10 candidates who qualified for the debates will appear Wednesday on the same stage.

headline_main: Analysis of Night 1 of the July Democratic Debates

abstract: The CNN debate was a clash over health care with moderates along the edge throwing firebombs on the electability of progressives with the boldest policy plans.
snippet: The CNN debate was a clash over health care with moderates along the edge throwing firebombs on the electability of progressives with the boldest policy plans.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — It was one of the most substantive presidential primary debates in recent memory, and the two Democratic candidates with the most ambitious plans dominated the stage.
